    "summary": "I did my MSc and PhD (2000-2004) in Materials Science at Delft University in the Netherlands, both on molecular dynamics simulations of physical vapour deposition of thin metal films. As part of my PhD I also learned to do DFT. That was my main research tool during the two postdoc jobs on radiation damage in Fe alloys that I did after my PhD, in Belfast and Edinburgh. After my postdoc job in Edinburgh I moved back to Delft University, where I did a number of postdoc jobs on different subjects, including atomistic simulation of ionic liquids interacting with solid surfaces, FeZnAl intermetallics (for Ruhr Universit\u00e4t Bochum, Germany, working from Delft) and graphene on Cu surfaces. Then I did a postdoc in atomistic simulation at the DIFFER institute in Eindhoven, looking a W surfaces exposed to plasma, among other things. Then it was back to Delft for more postdoc jobs on CALPHAD calculations to model phase stability of high entropy alloys and yet more radiation damage in nuclear alloys. The latter was extended by a short postdoc contract at the University of Lille.",
